article.description: Mount St. Mary's beats St. Francis (Pa) 52-40
article.headline: Mount St. Mary's beats St. Francis (Pa) 52-40
article.linkText: Mount St. Mary's beats St. Francis (Pa) 52-40
article.story: EMMITSBURG, Md. -- Junior Robinson scored 10 points, Byron Ashe added nine, and Mount St. Mary's beat St. Francis (Pa.) 52-40 on Saturday, handing the Red Flash their third straight loss and their ninth straight loss to the Mountaineers. Gregory Graves scored seven points and grabbed eight rebounds for Mount St. Mary's (9-10, 5-3 Northeast), who has held each of its past six opponents to under 65 points. St. Francis led 11-7 on a 3 by Malik Harmon, but the Mountaineers stayed close and there were five lead changes before Chris Martin made a jumper with seven seconds left to give Mount St. Mary's a 23-22 halftime lead. The Red Flash went scoreless for four minutes and the Mountaineers led 40-31 with 7:50 left after a layup by Taylor Danaher. Robinson scored the game's final seven points for the Mountaineers. Harmon led the Red Flash (10-9, 4-4) with 15 points and Earl Brown had 13 points and 13 boards.
